to see ip :
ip a
ifconfig

netstat  => used to see what connection are on and connected (ex: sending or reciving of data)
route => connection to where it can connect

network 
   on the network: sudo nmcli networking on
   sudo service NetworkManager (start,restart,stop)
   go to setting change : adapter connection (nat or bridge)

netstat -nano : what port are opend and connection

echo "ip dns" | sudo tee -a /etc/hosts
tee is run with sudo, while redirection (>) is handled by the shell before sudo is applied.
